DF = pd.concat(FRAMES, ignore_index=True)

Assessing Summary¶

There are no duplicate values
There're some null values that needs to be handled
A lot of datatypes needs to be transformed
start_time and end_time needs to be splitted into DAY, MONTH
Ther's some columns that's not necessary in our analysis methods

SOLUTIONS OF NAN VALUES:¶

WE CAN DROP 11771 ROWS THAT DOESN'T HAVE THE PICKUP AND DROPOFF STATION INFO (start_station_id\start_station_name, end_station_id\end_station_name). WE CAN FILL THE MISSING VALUES OF MEMBER's INFO (member_birth_year, member_gender)

In [60]:
## CREATE START\END (DAY, MONTH, YEAR, HOUR) COLUMNs SEPARATELY
DF_COPY['START_DAY'] = DF_COPY['start_time'].dt.strftime('%A')
DF_COPY['START_MONTH'] = DF_COPY['start_time'].dt.strftime('%B')
DF_COPY['START_YEAR'] = DF_COPY['start_time'].dt.year
DF_COPY['START_HOUR'] = DF_COPY['start_time'].dt.strftime('%H')

DF_COPY['END_DAY'] = DF_COPY['end_time'].dt.strftime('%A')
DF_COPY['END_MONTH'] = DF_COPY['end_time'].dt.strftime('%B')
DF_COPY['END_YEAR'] = DF_COPY['end_time'].dt.year
DF_COPY['END_HOUR'] = DF_COPY['end_time'].dt.strftime('%H')

DF_COPY['DURATION_MINUTES'] = DF_COPY['duration_sec']/60
DF_COPY['MEMBER_AGE'] = 2018 - DF_COPY['member_birth_year']

SUMMARY:¶

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

   ** The Dataset Contains 1863721 Observations, and 16 Features presents forg go-bike trips in 2018

New Features I Made That're Useful in our story?¶

   ** START_DAY, START_MONTH, and START_HOUR That're created from start_date, hence doing same from end_date 
   ** DURATION_MINUTES, This Column Represents the Duration in Minutes
   ** MEMBER AGE, THIS COLUMN IS CREATED BY THE YEAR OF THE WHOLE TRIPS (2018) WITH THE member_birth_year column

  • THE PEAK POINT IS IN OCTOBER

def hexbin(x, y, color, **kwargs):
    cmap = sns.light_palette(color, as_cmap=True)
    plt.hexbin(x, y, gridsize=15, cmap=cmap, **kwargs)

with sns.axes_style("dark"):
    g = sns.FacetGrid(DF_COPY, hue="user_type", col="user_type", height=4)
g.map(hexbin, "DURATION_MINUTES", "START_HOUR", extent=[0, 50, 0, 10]);

SUMMARY:¶

  • SUBSCIRBERS & CUSTOMERS HAVE SIGNIFICANT VARIATION, SUBSCIRBERS ARE CONSITENT AS THEY HAVE A FIXED SCHEDULE ,HAVE LESS DURATIONS THAN CUSTOMERS.
  • IN CONTRAST WITH CUSTOMERS, WHO HAVE CYCLING INCREASE ON SPECIALLY IN WEEKENDS.
  • CUSTOMERS ARE MORE LEISURLY ORIENTED HOWEVER THERE MIGHT BE FEW CUSTOMERS WHO SOMETIMES USES BIKE TO COMMUTE FROM OFFICE AS THERE IS A STEEP INCREASE IN CUSTOMERS TOO AT 8AM AND 5PM.
